  "text": "and the inverse mno transformation, which transfers the mno back to the abc coordinates, is given by [CITATION_1] where M \u22121 m no is defined as the transpose matrix of (5) M Matrixes (5) and (7) are continuously adjusted by six timedependent angles (\u03b8 a , \u03b8 b , \u03b8 c , \u03c6 a , \u03c6 b , \u03c6 c ), named mno angles, which are updated depending on the reference normal vector, as will be shown below.",
